From vobencha at fhcrc.org  Tue Sep 30 22:31:18 2014
From: vobencha at fhcrc.org (Valerie Obenchain)
Date: Tue, 30 Sep 2014 13:31:18 -0700
Subject: [Bioc-devel] Cannot interact with a BigWig file on the web with
 rtracklayer (Windows specific)
In-Reply-To: <6421_1412089534_542AC6BD_6421_9340_2_CAP8VEO6DoxfFTuFJQJjiKmi7HtGhBHqhf3o8TZ4C6ieqQG1Q8Q@mail.gmail.com>
References: <6421_1412089534_542AC6BD_6421_9340_2_CAP8VEO6DoxfFTuFJQJjiKmi7HtGhBHqhf3o8TZ4C6ieqQG1Q8Q@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <542B1316.1050003@fhcrc.org>

Hi,

Import and manipulation of BigWig files in rtracklayer make use of the 
Kent C library and are not supported on windows.

This is documented at

?import.bw
?`BigWigFile-class`

This problem isn't specific to an 'over the network' example. Trying to 
import() a local BigWig on Windows will also fail.

Valerie


On 09/30/2014 08:00 AM, Leonardo Collado Torres wrote:
